# Stakr - Default Rules

## CORE DEVELOPMENT PRINCIPLES

- Always prioritize fairness, verification integrity, and anti-abuse
- Avoid pay-to-win mechanics at all costs
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Write self-documenting code with clear variable names
- Use proper error handling for all operations
- Implement proper logging for debugging
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Follow the existing codebase patterns and conventions
- Write clear commit messages
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces
- Implement proper error boundaries in React components
- Use proper loading states for async operations
- Implement proper empty states for lists and data
- Use proper accessibility attributes (aria-labels, roles)
- Implement proper keyboard navigation
- Use proper semantic HTML elements
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles
- Optimize for performance and user experience

## CODE QUALITY

- Use ESLint and Prettier for code formatting
- Write meaningful comments for complex logic
- Use proper TypeScript strict mode
- Implement proper null checking and error handling
- Use proper async/await patterns
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper React hooks patterns
- Implement proper state management
- Use proper component composition
- Implement proper prop validation
- Use proper CSS-in-JS or Tailwind patterns
- Implement proper responsive design
- Use proper image optimization
- Implement proper SEO meta tags
- Use proper caching strategies

## NEW FEATURE REQUIREMENTS

- All new features must be tested before implementation
- All new components must be mobile-first and accessible
- All new API endpoints must include proper authentication
- All new features must follow Stakr's fairness principles
- All new code must include proper error handling
- All new features must include proper loading states
- All new features must include proper empty states
- All new features must be documented
- All new features must be optimized for performance
- All new features must include proper logging
- All new features must be accessible (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- All new features must work on mobile devices
- All new features must include proper TypeScript types
- All new features must follow existing naming conventions
- All new features must include proper state management

## COMPONENT DEVELOPMENT

- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper prop validation with TypeScript
- Use proper component composition patterns
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper loading and error states
- Implement proper accessibility (aria-labels, roles, keyboard navigation)
- Use proper responsive design patterns
- Implement proper mobile touch interactions
- Use proper semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper focus management
- Use proper animation and transition patterns
- Implement proper form validation
- Use proper data fetching patterns
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use proper performance optimization techniques

